    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem                                                                                                         \n\nfloatwin breaks display of multibyte characters at window boundary.\n\n### Steps to reproduce                                                                                              \n\n1. launch `nvim --clean`\n\n2. Sourcing following lua code\n\n```lua\nvim.cmd('tabnew | setlocal buftype=nofile bufhidden=wipe noswapfile')\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { 'あ' })\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, false, { 'あ' })\nlocal win = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf, false, {\n  relative = 'win',\n  row = 0,\n  col = 2,\n  width = 2,\n  height = 1,\n})\n```\n\nShow floating window contains `あ` and base buffer is look empty. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDisplay properly.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-872+gc54682f75-dirty\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo. it is problem of floatwin.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nPuTTY\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n                                                                                                                      \nscreen-256color\n                                                                                                                      \n### Installation\n                                                                                                                      \nfrom source\n",
    "closed_at": "2023-08-18T04:08:20Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This seems to fix the problem:\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c b/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c\r\nindex 59e9f71a6..e9b23d129 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/ui_compositor.c\r\n@@ -402,7 +402,7 @@ static void compose_line(Integer row, Integer startcol, Integer endcol, LineFlag\r\n       if (col == endcol - 1) {\r\n         skipend = 0;\r\n       }\r\n-    } else if (n > 1 && linebuf[col - startcol + 1][0] == NUL) {\r\n+    } else if (col == startcol && n > 1 && linebuf[1][0] == NUL) {\r\n       skipstart = 0;\r\n     }\r\n \r\n```",
